de.wwu.muggl.symbolic.generating
Interface GeneratorProvider

All Superinterfaces:
GenericGeneratorProvider
All Known Implementing Classes:
DoubleIncrementGeneratorProvider, DoubleMultiplicationGeneratorProvider, IntegerIncrementGeneratorProvider
public interface GeneratorProvider
extends GenericGeneratorProvider

Interface for generator providers.

Generators are unlikely to have empty constructors. They will have a constructor that accepts arguments and or multiple constructors to offer customizability. In order to be able to utilize a generator with customizable settings and not having the need to put the setting into the generator itself, generators cannot be directly used but need an appropriate GeneratorProvider that instantiates them. These providers have to implement this interface and to have an empty constructor in order to be accepted as feasible providers.
